cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.CL. 

The paper deals with video learning, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category. The paper proposes a novel learning algorithm that allows for online and incremental learning of weakly annotated video data, which falls under the category of machine learning. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely category. The paper also includes explicit context and length modeling, which involves natural language processing techniques, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another possible category. Since the paper deals with video segmentation and labeling tasks, cs.MM (Multimedia) is also a likely category. Finally, since the paper involves modeling and labeling of video data, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is another possible category.
